# NORM
data_long <- Data %>%
  pivot_longer(everything(), names_to = "Item", values_to = "Response")
head(data_long)
## # A tibble: 6  2
##   Item       Response
##   <chr>         <int>
## 1 ownership         1
## 2 usage_freq        2
## 3 usingSince        4
## 4 typicalUse        4
## 5 brand             1
## 6 cost              1
# Make sure responses are factors with proper ordering
data_long$Response <- factor(data_long$Response, levels = sort(unique(unlist(Data))))

# Plot: one bar chart per item
ggplot(data_long, aes(x = Response)) +
  geom_bar(fill = "steelblue") +
  facet_wrap(~ Item, scales = "free_y") +
  labs(title = "Distributions", x = "Response", y = "Count") +
  theme_minimal()
